WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.868 --> 00:00:06.100
♪♪

00:00:06.100 --> 00:00:08.234
JANUARY 10, 1992.

00:00:08.234 --> 00:00:10.300
A CONTAINER SHIP TRAVELING
FROM HONG KONG

00:00:10.300 --> 00:00:11.701
TO TACOMA, WASHINGTON,

00:00:11.701 --> 00:00:13.434
LOSES 12 CONTAINERS OVERBOARD.

00:00:13.434 --> 00:00:15.100
ONE OF THEM SETS LOOSE

00:00:15.100 --> 00:00:17.968
THOUSANDS OF TINY,
YELLOW, PLASTIC DUCKS

00:00:17.968 --> 00:00:19.834
ON THE CURRENTS
OF THE NORTH PACIFIC.

00:00:19.834 --> 00:00:22.901
Narrator:
THE CURRENTS CARRY THE DUCKS
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

00:00:25.033 --> 00:00:26.701
SO, MONTHS LATER,
THEY START WASHING UP

00:00:26.701 --> 00:00:28.300
ON THE COAST OF ALASKA,

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:31.467
TURNING THIS TOY SPILL
INTO AN ACCIDENTAL EXPERIMENT.

00:00:31.467 --> 00:00:32.801
SO, FROM THE DUCKY STUDY,

00:00:32.801 --> 00:00:34.667
YOU GET REAL-TIME DATA

00:00:34.667 --> 00:00:37.033
ABOUT THE CURRENTS
IN THE NORTH PACIFIC.

00:00:37.033 --> 00:00:39.167
Narrator:
THE ACCIDENTAL DUCK EXPERIMENT

00:00:39.167 --> 00:00:42.601
IS STILL PROVIDING INFORMATION
TODAY.

00:00:42.601 --> 00:00:44.200
THEY'RE ALMOST INDESTRUCTIBLE.

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:46.734
I MEAN, LITERALLY 20 YEARS
AFTER THEY HIT THE OCEAN,

00:00:46.734 --> 00:00:48.801
THEY'RE STILL WASHING UP
ON BEACHES AROUND THE WORLD.

